Pfizer Inc. said its Quigley Co. subsidiary acquired most of the assets of Zedmark Refractories Corp. 

Terms weren't disclosed. 

The acquisition represents a diversification for Quigley, a supplier of shapes, coatings, clad alloy wire and calcium metal products for the iron and steel industry.
Zedmark is a Slippery Rock, Pa., maker of specialty glass refractories, which is used to mold bottles, laboratory glassware and fine tableware. 

